{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:proverbs.21",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 21,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 21 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:1",
      "text": "As a rush of water, so is the king's heart in God's hand: he turns it whithersoever he may desire to point out.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:2",
      "text": "Every man seems to himself righteous; but the Lord directs the hearts.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:3",
      "text": "To do justly and to speak truth, are more pleasing to God than the blood of sacrifices.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:4",
      "text": "A high-minded man is stout-hearted in his pride; and the lamp of the wicked is sin.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:6",
      "text": "He that gathers treasures with a lying tongue pursues vanity on to the snares of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:7",
      "text": "Destruction shall lodge with the ungodly; for they refuse to do justly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:8",
      "text": "To the froward God sends froward ways; for his works are pure and right.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:9",
      "text": "It is better to dwell in a corner on the house-top, than in plastered rooms with unrighteousness, and in an open house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:10",
      "text": "The soul of the ungodly shall not be pitied by any man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:11",
      "text": "When an intemperate man is punished the simple becomes wiser: and a wise man understanding will receive knowledge.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:12",
      "text": "A righteous man understands the hearts of the ungodly: and despises the ungodly for their wickedness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:13",
      "text": "He that stops his ears from hearing the poor, himself also shall cry, and there shall be none to hear him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:14",
      "text": "A secret gift calms anger: but he that forbears to give stirs up strong wrath.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:15",
      "text": "It is the joy of the righteous to do judgment: but a holy man is abominable with evil-doers.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:16",
      "text": "A man that wanders out of the way of righteousness, shall rest in the congregation of giants.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:17",
      "text": "A poor man loves mirth, loving wine and oil in abundance;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:18",
      "text": "and a transgressor is the abomination of a righteous man.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:19",
      "text": "It is better to dwell in a wilderness than with a quarrelsome and talkative and passionate woman.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:20",
      "text": "A desirable treasure will rest on the mouth of the wise; but foolish men will swallow it up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:21",
      "text": "The way of righteousness and mercy will find life and glory.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:22",
      "text": "A wise man assaults strong cities, and demolishes the fortress in which the ungodly trusted.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:23",
      "text": "He that keeps his mouth and his tongue keeps his soul from trouble.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:24",
      "text": "A bold and self-willed and insolent man is called a pest: and he that remembers injuries is a transgressor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:25",
      "text": "Desires kill the sluggard; for his hands do not choose to do anything.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.26",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:26",
      "text": "An ungodly man entertains evil desires all the day: but the righteous is unsparingly merciful and compassionate.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.27",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:27",
      "text": "The sacrifices of the ungodly are abomination to the Lord, for they offer them wickedly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.28",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:28",
      "text": "A false witness shall perish; but an obedient man will speak cautiously.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.29",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:29",
      "text": "An ungodly man impudently withstands with his face; but the upright man himself understands his ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.30",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:30",
      "text": "There is no wisdom, there is no courage, there is no counsel against the ungodly.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:proverbs.21.31",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 21,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 21:31",
      "text": "A horse is prepared for the day of battle; but help is of the Lord.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
